GCC Stock Markets Lost $12.2 Billion in May, Times of Oman Says

-- B y   V i v i a n   S a l a m a
-- 
2011-06-25T06:25:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-25/gcc-stock-markets-lost-12-2-billion-in-may-times-of-oman-says.html
Stock markets in the six-member Gulf
Cooperation Council lost a total of $12.2 billion in May to
bring the market value of companies listed on them to $757.9
billion as political tensions and light liquidity prompted a
sell-off, The Times of Oman  reported today , citing research by
Kamco Asset Management Company.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vivian Salama in  Abu Dhabi  at 
 vsalama@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net  